                            <comment id="12918954" author="thejas" created="Thu, 7 Oct 2010 17:17:45 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1666&quot; title=&quot;union onschema fails when the input relation has cast from bytearray to another type&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-1666&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-1666&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.1.patch &lt;br/&gt;
When union onschema is used, TypeCheckingValidator is called more than once. But lineage information set  in fieldschema of LOCast during first invocation of TypeCheckingValidator was still there, causing issues with the lineage logic. The patch fixes it. I have also added checks to TypeCheckingVisitor to check for any conflicting lineage information for LOCast . &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unit tests and test-patch have passed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
